## How to Access Skills in Cursor

Use the `Read` tool on skill files. Skills may be at:
- `~/.cursor/skills/superpowers/skills/{skill-name}/SKILL.md` (user-level)
- `.cursor/skills/superpowers/skills/{skill-name}/SKILL.md` (project-level)

**Available skills:**
- `brainstorming` - Interactive design refinement before implementation
- `test-driven-development` - RED-GREEN-REFACTOR cycle
- `systematic-debugging` - 4-phase root cause process
- `writing-plans` - Detailed implementation plans
- `executing-plans` - Batch execution with checkpoints
- `subagent-driven-development` - Fast iteration with two-stage review
- `using-git-worktrees` - Parallel development branches
- `finishing-a-development-branch` - Merge/PR decision workflow
